e beginning of this chapter) and finally answered: “It is heavy to say, but I think war excluded. When I young was, I came upon the idea of supposing only the best” (he all but turned “best” into “pest,” so gross were his lip-consonants). “I hold this idea always. The chief thing by me is optimismus.”

“Which comes in very handy, seeing your profession,” said I with a smile.

He lowered at me and replied quite seriously:

“But it is pessimismus that gives clients to us.”
